-- Hellenic Telecom Closer to Satellite Unit Sale, Imerisia Says
-- B y   T o m   S t o u k a s
-- 2012-07-04T08:38:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/hellenic-telecom-closer-to-satellite-unit-sale-imerisia-says.html
Hellenic Telecommunications
Organization SA (HTO)  is close to getting Greek government approval to
start the process of selling its Hellas Sat unit,  Imerisia 
reported, without citing anyone.  Hellenic Telecom  has hired a consultant to assess the
satellite unit, which is likely to bring in 150 million euros
($189 million), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Stoukas in Athens at 
 astoukas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  